<dl id="n41198c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41198c">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41198c"> 198(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> baby of a girl friend / of his, smthg very / strange about children</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[L.C., commenting on a photograph]</font> &ldquo;That is the <mark>baby of a girl friend of mine</mark>&rdquo;, he said, and then, with an absolute change of voice, &ldquo;there is <mark>something very strange about very young children</mark>, something I cannot understand&rdquo;. ... I cannot remember all he said, but some of his remarks still remain with me. He said that in the company of very little children his brain enjoyed a rest which was startlingly recuperative. ... I understood him to say that the effect was almost physical! <small> Miss Isa Bowman, <a name="IBSL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#IBSL"><cite title="source">The Story Of Lewis Carroll</cite></a>. (1899) 59</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
